'''Continuous optimization''' is a branch of [[Optimization (mathematics)|optimization]] in [[applied mathematics]].

As opposed to [[discrete optimization]], the [[Variable (mathematics)|variables]] used in the [[objective function]] are required to be [[continuous variable]]s&mdash;that is, to be chosen from a set of [[real number|real]] values between which there are no gaps (values from [[Interval (mathematics)|interval]]s of the [[real line]]). Because of this [[continuity (mathematics)|continuity]] assumption, continuous optimization allows the use of [[calculus]] techniques.

[[Category:Mathematical optimization]]


